<subSubSection id="785740A925437B5A3C9AAB8F9A4E83B4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="47BE9A6279C06654C3404637A1D4F4D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C64EE434E2BBBB70A07596532E9DFDD5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is usually easily recognised by its large carolla and the palmately-lobed discolorous leaves. However, as with many species in the 
<taxonomicName id="FBC9665E972D0F75815E813786AA8BB2" authority="" authorityName="" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Pharbitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pharbitis</taxonomicName>
Clade, the leaves may be entire or lobed. 
<emphasis id="02232D6B6E5A4EA12FD18965CD02B97E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gentry</emphasis>
1788 and 
<emphasis id="A95EAF05D89B6C062CE2D55B8F6E7889" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ruiz et al.</emphasis>
2009-278 differ from other specimens in having entire, strongly abaxially sericeous leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5629517483017E586166641966A17C87" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Placement of this species in the 
<taxonomicName id="3C823812FE4BF58BDFCB67F7C89EA81B" authority="" authorityName="" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Pharbitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pharbitis</taxonomicName>
Clade is provisional.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
